Bursting through the clouds and scattering a flock of birds, Grimlock
continued to follow the transport vehicle. Like a missile he tried to
make body contact with it, but was always one step behind it, until he
began to hear some kind of announcing over large speakers. He ignored it
however, nothing was more important than rescuing the Autobots, Pacifix
already dropped the ball, and Grimlock needed to pick it up and run with
it.
------------------------------------------------------------------------

Firedrill followed on the ground, and could now see the massive Obylisk.
In normal circumstances he would have been in awe of it, but his mentor
was in trouble. "Hang on Cliffjumper, I'm coming." he screamed, the rage
taking over him.
------------------------------------------------------------------------

Strafe ran up to Scattershot, "Sir, Strafe is in trouble, we must help
him." He pleaded, wanting to just take off for the robots.
